normalization_record.normalized_question_text:
A small ball with mass $m=0.1\mathrm{kg}$ is thrown horizontally from point $O$ at the right end of a horizontal platform with an initial velocity $v_{0}$. After leaving the platform, the ball falls tangentially into a vertical smooth circular track $ABC$ at point $A$ and just passes through the highest point $C$ along the track. The track is part of a circle of radius $R=2.5\mathrm{m}$ with a $127^{\circ}$ arc at the upper left removed. $CB$ is the vertical diameter. Given $\sin53^{\circ}=0.8$, $\cos53^{\circ}=0.6$, $g=10\mathrm{m}/\mathrm{s}^{2}$, and neglecting air resistance, find:
1. the speed $v_C$ of the ball at point $C$;
2. the magnitude of the supporting force exerted by the track on the ball at the lowest point $B$;
3. the vertical height $H$ from point $O$ to point $A$.

